---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<BaseHead 
  title={`FIPS 140-3 Level 3 Certified Encryption Recommendation | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
  description="Our independent security recommendation: the iStorage datAshur PRO+C, a FIPS 140-3 Level 3 certified hardware-encrypted flash drive."
/>

<link href="https://unpkg.com/aos@2.3.1/dist/aos.css" rel="stylesheet" />

<Header />

<main>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-background">
      <div class="floating-orb orb-1"></div>
      <div class="floating-orb orb-2"></div>
      <div class="floating-orb orb-3"></div>
      <div class="floating-orb orb-4"></div>
      <div class="grid-overlay"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 data-aos="fade-up">Independent Recommendation for High-Assurance Data Protection</h1>

        <p class="tagline" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
          When your organisation requires more than standard encryption, certified hardware security becomes essential.
        </p>

        <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
          We do not sell encrypted storage devices. Instead, we analyse and evaluate
          certified security products and recommend solutions that meet stringent
          protection requirements. One device stands out for portable, tamper-resistant,
          independently validated protection.
        </p>

        <div class="cta-buttons" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="300">
          <a href="/consultation" class="btn primary">Request a Security Consultation</a>
          <a href="/about-us" class="btn secondary">How We Evaluate Products</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="scroll-indicator">
      <div class="chevron"></div>
      <div class="chevron"></div>
      <div class="chevron"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <section class="main-content">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- PRODUCT RECOMMENDATION -->
      <div class="section product-showcase" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2>Our Recommended Certified Hardware-Encrypted Drive</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          After reviewing currently available certified hardware-encrypted storage devices,
          we recommend the <strong>iStorage datAshur PRO+C</strong> for organisations requiring
          certified, tamper-resistant, portable data security.
        </p>

        <div class="product-feature">
          <div class="product-header">
            <h3 class="product-name">iStorage datAshur PRO+C</h3>
            <div class="product-badge">FIPS 140-3 Level 3 Certified</div>
          </div>

          <p class="product-description">
            The datAshur PRO+C is one of the first portable storage devices to achieve
            FIPS 140-3 Level 3 validation â€” the highest assurance level currently available
            for commercial removable media. This level of certification requires hardened,
            tamper-resistant hardware, secure key management, strict anti-tamper controls,
            and protection against physical compromise.
          </p>

          <div class="specs-grid">

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="100">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>Independent Certification</strong>
                <span>
                  Validated to FIPS 140-3 Level 3, including hardened tamper-resistant construction,
                  role-based authentication, and secure key storage.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="150">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>Encryption Architecture</strong>
                <span>
                  Full-disk AES-XTS 256-bit hardware encryption performed entirely on the device,
                  ensuring encryption keys never touch a host system.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="200">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>Tamper-Resistant Electronics</strong>
                <span>
                  Internal components are encapsulated in a protective resin barrier designed to
                  reveal and resist probing, drilling, voltage manipulation, or physical intrusion.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="250">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>On-Device PIN Entry</strong>
                <span>
                  Access is controlled through an integrated keypad, preventing keylogging and
                  ensuring authentication occurs before the device connects to any computer.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="300">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>Brute-Force Attack Countermeasures</strong>
                <span>
                  After a defined number of incorrect PIN attempts, the device cryptographically
                  erases its keys and permanently prevents further access, protecting data even if
                  the device is stolen.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="350">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>Auto-Lock, Unattended Lock, and Reset</strong>
                <span>
                  Automatically locks on removal or after a defined idle period, with an optional
                  full device reset that securely destroys all keys and credentials.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="400">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>Rugged Construction</strong>
                <span>
                  Aluminium alloy casing with IP68 dust and water resistance, crush protection,
                  and resistance to environmental stress.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="450">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>System Compatibility</strong>
                <span>
                  OS-agnostic operation. Works with Windows, macOS, Linux, thin clients,
                  virtualised systems, and embedded devices without drivers or software.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-item" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="500">
              <div class="spec-content">
                <strong>Performance</strong>
                <span>
                  USB 3.2 Gen 1 interface with typical real-world read speeds of approximately
                  300 MB/s and write speeds around 200+ MB/s depending on capacity.
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- NOT A SALES OFFER -->
      <div class="section" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h4>Important Notice</h4>
        <p>
          We are not an authorised reseller or distributor of the datAshur PRO+C or any other
          encrypted storage device. Our recommendation is based purely on independent technical
          evaluation and suitability for high-assurance data protection requirements.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- FINAL CTA -->
      <div class="section final-cta" data-aos="zoom-in">
        <h2>Determine Whether You Need Certified Hardware</h2>
        <p>
          Not every organisation requires FIPS 140-3 validated hardware. We can help you assess
          whether your operational risk profile, compliance regime, and threat exposure justify
          a certified device of this class.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="/consultation" class="btn primary large">Book a Security Assessment</a>
          <a href="mailto:contact@hermetrix.nz?subject=Hardware%20Security%20Inquiry" class="btn secondary">
            Contact Us for Guidance
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<Footer />

<script is:client src="https://unpkg.com/aos@2.3.1/dist/aos.js"></script>
<script is:client>
  AOS.init({
    duration: 800,
    once: true,
    offset: 100
  });
</script>
